> From what I understand, a byproduct of the combustion of propane is water 
> vapor.  It seems to me that the water vapor I released inside my bus 
> condensed on my tools (and who knows what else inside; inside doors, etc) 
> as things cooled.  While the catalytic element makes the combustion safe 
> for us to breathe, the water is still there.  Has anyone else seen 
> condensation inside their bus from using one of these heaters?  I thought 
> I'd bring it up since it seems to me I've noticed several list members 
> using these heaters.

